I can do a fairly simple game to get you used to it.
See the little icon next to "Leave" with people and a 6 in it?
When the game is on, you will press that icon to either use any power you have at night, or to vote for people during the day
There will be 4 roles in the game. 1 Wolf, 1 Stalker, 1 Protector, 2 Vanilla Villagers, and 1 Sleepwalker (who is told they are a Vanilla Villager, so they don't realise they are a Sleepwalker)
Werewolf is normal, during the night, try and kill someone, during the day, lie about what you are :)
Stalker - each night, you can choose to follow another player, and you will see if they 'visit' another player.
Protector - Each night, you can choose to protect someone, including yourself. You cannot protect the same person 2 days in a row
Sleepwalker - Will be told they are a Villager, but will secretly 'visit' someone at night. You won't learn anything and you won't know who you visited.
You can find more about how we play at this link, and also to learn the roles - https://werewolv.es/guides/how-to-play-online-werewolf
It's the link the "How to Play" button on top links to.
When the game starts, we'll all be given a different identity to post as, so you won't know who is who.
The day will be 4 minutes long, and the night will be one minute.
We also have longer games that have 12 hour days and 12 hour nights.
You can tell the difference, because they will be called ext-123 or whatever
And if you click the Discord link at the top of the screen, you can join our discord, where we talk about werewolf and lots more stuff and you can get notifications when games are ready to play.
